I don't like Mango and Mango pulp ?

What we in India consider a cheesecake is not really a cheesecake. For the real thing, take catch a flight to NYC and take a yellow cab to Junior’s for a slice. 

Until then, bake this superb, light, airy creation by @vardaan4, who works with #ScrollChefOfTheMonth @suvirsaran. Happy Sunday! ? 

Ingredients:
FOR BISCUIT BASE
1 packet digestive biscuits
30 gm salted butter 
FOR FILLING
100 gm mango pulp
100 gm cream cheese
100 gm whipped cream
50 gm white chocolate
40 gm powdered sugar

Preparation:
Blitz the biscuit into fine crumbs in a food processor. Add butter and blitz until combined.
Pour into prepared cake pan and press down firmly.
Place in a preheated oven at 180C for 7-8 mins.
In a mixing bowl, mix the powdered sugar and cream cheese until there are no lumps. Spoon in the mango pulp.
Melt white chocolate and add to the above mixture
Whip cream till medium-stiff peaks form, fold it in the above mixture.
Pour the mix into the prepared cake pan and chill for 4-6 hours.
Garnish with fresh mangoes.

Visit @ScrollFood for more such amazing recipes.

Read Caption: 
Started with a swipe on Bumble a few days back, as I thought to pass some time during this lockdown. We have not met each other yet. I don’t know how will it be to look at them for the first time, I don’t know how will it be to meet them for the first time, I don’t know how will it be to kiss them for the first time, I don’t know how I will feel when my arms will be holding them so tight. As I think about them and these sublime feelings I get goose bumps. 
Our first date will be at their favorite coffee shop, sipping on their favorite coffee, having endless conversations about life, music and adventures. We are two different people: they like eating healthy and I like eating all the unhealthy food I can find. Our idea of life is different, but who cares as long as we are having fun. We are two souls lost in the casual imagination of life, protecting our hearts from the complexity of love. Though its casual, I would still want to capture their actions in my photographic memory.

node.text:
Baked this Homemade Chocolate Oreo cake - 5 mins microwave bake receipe for a friends birthday. 
Ingredients:
For sponge -
1) 240 gms of chocolate Oreo Biscuit
2) 1 cup of milk ( room temperature)
3) 1 tsp ENO ( I used lemon flavour)

For frosting -
1) Hershey's chocolate syrup
2) Homemade condensed milk

For decoration -
1) Oreo original biscuit
2) Dukes Waffy choco rolls
3) Chocolate pieces

Receipe:
Grind the Oreo biscuits and transfer them to a whisking bowl. Now start adding milk while swiftly whisking the batter. Ensure to add milk gradually and not at one go. Once a thick creamy consistency is formed, keep the batter aside. Now grease the baking tin with butter or refined oil. Before pouring the batter into tin, add ENO to the mix and gently mix it using cut and fold method. Make sure to not over whisk the batter post adding ENO. And now immediately pour the batter in tin.
Put the tin in microwave and set the timer for 5 mins. Take out the tin and your nice fluffy sponge is ready. Keep the sponge to cool down.

P.S. I decorated the cake since it was a friend's birthday. You can have the simply baked cake sponge with coffee or tea. It will taste awesome! 
For layering and decoration: 
Before layering the sponges, I have sprayed them with sugar syrup to make it little moist. While layering, I used the chocolate syrup. It helps the sponge to stick together and gives a good flavour as well. For decoration, I have randomly arrange Oreo original biscuits and chocolate pieces over condensed milk which I poured on the top most sponge. On the sides I have arranged choco waffle rolls. To make the rolls stick to the sponge, you can use the choclate syrup or Hershey's cocoa spread.

Note: 
1) For a 3 tier cake like mine, I baked 3 cake sponges. 
2) No oven pre heating required.

node.text:
SUNDAY PUDDING
.
For a bake free dessert, there is something candid about a gloriously spiced Tiramisu Pudding enveloped in a velvety cream. Elegant yet simple, it is swift, light and fluffy. It embodies all the nuances of the autumn perfume - ginger, cinnamon and caramel, blurring the absence of coffee.
.
Embellished with their flecks of spices and sparkles of sugar peeking through the velvety cream, the crushed cookies is flamboyantly charismatic.
.
Using crushed lotus biscoff biscuits, provides a toothsome contrast to the usual boudoir lady fingers. The taste is opulent and rich yet it is not as heavy as most desserts, quietly mollifying after a plump Sunday lunch. You can either serve it from a large bowl or prepare individual servings in pretty glasses or bowls.
.
The link to this recipe can be found in the profile. 

To shop my ebook, head over to the link in bio.
.
